Bangs","startTime":null,"eventDescription":""The 21st century is lousy with bands thinking they're breaking a mold. Mostly, they limply and insufficiently retread tired ground through watered down interpretation. Thing is, though, there's no drug as powerful as nostalgia, whether you were actually there or not. But what of those artists that aren't memory hounds yet succeed brilliantly at, not nostalgia, but flat out déjà vu? In other words, those that don't trace the letters but know the actual language? Perfect sound forever is a great catch phrase but can rarely be accurately applied to, well, anything.

All of which is to say, welcome to the world of BLUNT BANGS.

Formed by guitarist/vocalist/songwriter Reggie Youngblood (Black Kids) during a sabbatical while writing his band's sophomore album the whole thing didn't have a name or lineup at first. He just wanted to write good, guitar-based pop songs that, as he says, "hit the sweet spots." So while still living in Jacksonville, FL he booked some studio time in Athens, GA and grabbed Gospel Music's Cash Carter to play drums. After some initial demos were done the pair took on bassist Ryan Vogel (Grape Soda) as well as second guitarist Ray Heekin, also of Gospel Music. While Heekin remained in the lineup long enough to make a record his departure was placated by guitarist/vocalist Christian "Smokey" DeRoeck and the Blunt Bangs lineup was finalized and totally solidified.

Youngblood isn't kidding about songs that hit the sweet spot. Good gravy, opening track "Florida Gurls" channels the ghosts of Big Star in enormous ways, "Sick Moves" is as Teenage Fanclub as anything to ever come out of Northern Britain (as is "Taylor Swift") but the real kicker comes on the second track "Keef." With vocals buried just enough for you to make out a few words but mostly write your own and a wonderfully lyric-less chorus of "yeah-eh-eh-eh-eh-eh-yeah" this is the one that moves the feet as much as the heart.

The seven songs on this record you've got in front of you are a ticket into the instantly remembered now. You've never heard these songs, yet, you've been here. There's the inescapable feeling that this has happened before. And, really, it has. It's happened in every record that made you play air guitar; every one you pulled off the shelf to make that perfect mixtape for a long lost crush; every one that pulled at your heart through the power of melody, a well placed guitar solo, a single poignant lyric, or any of the other myriad, painfully inarticulate reasons we fall in love with specific records."","isMobileFriendly":"false","image":null,"youtubeVideos":[],"embedAudio":"","embedVideo":"","urlAudio":"","urlPurchaseMusic":"","urlOfficialWebsite":"https://soundcloud.com/reggie-tv/sets/bangs/s-3oID0","urlMySpace":"","urlFacebook":"https://www.facebook.com/nightschoolisblessed/","urlTwitter":"","twitterScreenName":""}],"supports":[],"urlEventDetailsUrl":"http://www.ticketfly.com/event/1363341?utm_medium=api"}]}
